race.description: Brisbane Broncos Derby 1 Nov Class 1 Hcp
race.comment: EASY LOVE (3) was beaten less than a length over 1350m here fresh in a nice run. Fitter and extra trip a plus. Only run on wet ground was unplaced but close to the winner the trained in NSW. Worth following up. SAN GABRIEL (2) finished a fraction astern of EASY LOVE in the same race last time and should be at top now after two runs in. The extra ground helps now and Moor is expected to race forward. BERTUS (6) has been thereabouts last couple of starts but is better than that. Will appreciate any give in the ground as the soft track form is much better. DOINGITEASY (5) was an impressed winner last start at Murwillumbah over 1550m, albeit in an easier race. That was on a good track but did run well on heavy a few starts back when third. Claim helps and should run well.
